2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the design of a limited feedback codebook, which is relevant to wireless communication and networking. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the control and degrees of freedom in a MIMO system, which is relevant to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the performance gains of a 2D antenna array, which is relevant to multimedia applications such as video streaming. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses the design of a codebook based on Grassmannian line packing, which is relevant to game theory and optimization.
